          "principle": "P5",
          "principle_hash": "4bded803ae68a50cd50b79c414cf78674a825ce4d673c75f0f239c13046e184a",
          "claim": "Context: Silently skipping unreadable imports masks real problems",
          "smt2": "; PRINCIPLE: P5 - Semantic Correctness\n; Context: Silently skipping unreadable imports masks real problems\n; Analysis: What does downstream code expect?\n\n; After gatherImportSources returns, execute uses importSources in:\n; 1. buildCallSiteContext(signal, source, importSources, existingContracts)\n; 2. buildCallSiteContext receives importSources as parameter\n\n; If importSources is missing entries (due to read failures), downstream \n; context building operates on incomplete data\n\n; Model: What if 3 imports exist but only 2 are readable?\n(declare-const total_imports Int)\n(declare-const readable_imports Int)\n(declare-const failed_imports Int)\n\n; Code transition: loop processes each import\n(assert (= total_imports 3))\n(assert (= readable_imports 2))\n(assert (= failed_imports 1))\n\n; sources array only contains readable imports\n(assert (= readable_imports (- total_imports failed_imports)))\n(assert (= failed_imports 1))\n\n; Downstream code doesn't know import failed\n; May build incomplete context bundle\n\n(check-sat)\n; sat → silent failures create incomplete import sources\n; No indication to caller that data is missing"
        }
      ],
